Privacy policies
Last updated: February 10th, 2017
Pili Pop Labs S.A.S Privacy Policy
Pili Pop Labs S.A.S. (“Pili Pop Labs,” “we,” or “us”) welcomes you to www.pilipop.com and any and all applications or mobile applications offered by Pili Pop Labs S.A.S. Pili Pop Labs S.A.S (“Pili Pop Labs”), its parent and its subsidiaries respect the privacy rights of our users and are committed to protecting the information collected through its online products, online services and websites, including, but not limited to, “Pili Pop” mobile applications and Pili Pop website (together “Services”). Pili Pop
Labs collects, stores, and uses the information collected in connection with Pili Pop Labs’s Services.
BY INSTALLING, USING, REGISTERING TO OR OTHERWISE ACCESSING THE SERVICES, YOU AGREE TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY AND GIVE AN EXPLICIT AND INFORMED CONSENT TO THE PROCESSING OF YOUR PERSONAL DATA IN ACCORDANCE WITH THIS PRIVACY POLICY. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY, PLEASE DO NOT INSTALL, USE, REGISTER TO OR OTHERWISE ACCESS THE SERVICES.
Non-personal data
For purposes of this Privacy Policy, “non-personal data” means information that does not directly identify you. Additionally, non-personal data means “aggregate” and “de-personalized” information, which is data Pili Pop Labs collects about the use of Pili Pop Labs Services, from which any personally identifiable data has been removed. Pili Pop Labs is using tools or third party analytical softwares to automatically collect and use certain non-personal data that does not directly enable Pili Pop Labs to identify you. The softwares Pili Pop Labs are currently using are Flurry Analytics which is owned by Yahoo, and their Privacy Policy can be found here: https://info.yahoo.com/privacy/us/yahoo/ and Amplitude and their Privacy Policy can be found here: https://amplitude.com/privacy. The types of non-personal data Pili Pop Labs may collect and use include, but are not limited to: (i) device properties, including, but not limited to unique device identifier or other device identifier (“UDID”); (ii) device software platform and firmware; (iii) mobile phone carrier; (iv) game score and achievements; (v) other non-personal data as reasonably required by Pili Pop Labs to enhance the Services and other Pili Pop Labs products and services. Pili Pop Labs may use and disclose to Pili Pop Labs’ partners and contractors the collected non-personal data for purposes of analyzing usage of the Services, managing and providing the Services and to further develop the Services and other Pili Pop Labs services and products.
Ads
We do not allow advertising companies to collect data through our service for ad targeting.
Personal Data
For purposes of this Privacy Policy, “personal data” means personally identifiable information that specifically identifies you as an individual. Likely situations when you make personal data available to Pili Pop Labs include, but are not limited to: (i) registration for Services, contests and special events; (ii) accessing Services using a third party ID, such as social networking sites or gaming services; (iii) subscribing to newsletters; (iv) requesting technical support; and (v) otherwise through use of Pili Pop Labs Services where personal data is required for use and/or participation.
The types of personal data may vary depending on the type of activity you are engaged in. The personal data Pili Pop Labs may collect, process and use may include, but are not limited to the child’s first name, child’s birth date and parent’s e-mail address. Pili Pop Labs may use collected personal data for purposes of analyzing usage of the Services, providing customer and technical support, managing and providing Services and to further develop the Services and other Pili Pop Labs services and products. Pili Pop Labs may combine non-personal data with personal data. Pili Pop Labs may use your personal data to send messages to you with informative and/or commercial content about Pili Pop Labs’ services and services Pili Pop Labs thinks may be of interest to you, such as new features and services, special offers and updated information.
Disclosure and Transfer of Personal Dat
Pili Pop Labs collects and processes personal data on a voluntary basis and it is not in the business of selling your personal data to third parties. Personal data may, however, occasionally be disclosed in accordance with applicable legislation and this Privacy Policy. Additionally, Pili Pop Labs may disclose personal data to its parent companies and its subsidiaries in accordance with this Privacy Policy. Pili Pop Labs may use third party service providers such as email service providers, shipping agents, data analyzers and business intelligence providers. Pili Pop Labs has the right to share your personal data as necessary for the aforementioned third parties to provide their services for Pili Pop Labs. Pili Pop Labs is not liable for the acts and omissions of these third parties, except as provided by mandatory law. Pili Pop Labs may disclose your personal data to third parties as required by law enforcement or other government officials in connection with an investigation of fraud, intellectual property infringements, or other activity that is illegal or may expose you or Pili Pop Labs to legal liability. Pili Pop Labs may also disclose your personal data to third parties when Pili Pop Labs has a reason to believe that a disclosure is necessary to address potential or actual injury or interference with Pili Pop Labs’ rights, property, operations, users or others who may be harmed or may suffer loss or damage, or Pili Pop Labs believes that such disclosure is necessary to protect Pili Pop Labs’ rights, combat fraud and/or comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, or legal process served on Pili Pop Labs. To the extent permitted by applicable law, Pili Pop Labs will make reasonable efforts to notify you of such disclosure through Pili Pop Labs’ website or in another reasonable manner.
Data Retention and Correctness
Pili Pop Labs retains the data collected pursuant to this Privacy Policy for the period necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law. Thereafter if the collected data is no longer needed for purposes specified in this Privacy Policy, Pili Pop Labs deletes all aforementioned data in its possession within a reasonable timeframe. Pili Pop Labs does not verify the correctness of personal data. Pili Pop Labs may still retain some of the data to the extent such retention is necessary to resolve disputes, enforce Pili Pop Labs user agreements, and comply with technical and legal requirements and constraints related to the security, integrity and operation of Services.
Cookies, beacons and tracking
The Services may use “cookies” and other technologies such as pixel tags, clear GIFs and web beacons. Pili Pop Labs treats information collected by cookies and similar technologies as non-personal data. Emails and other electronic communications Pili Pop Labs sends to you may contain code that enables Pili Pop Labs to track your usage of the communication, including whether the communication was opened and/or what links were followed (if any). Pili Pop Labs may combine that information to other information Pili Pop Labs has about you and Pili Pop Labs may use that information to improve the Services and/or provide customized communications to you.
Third Party Terms and Conditions
Please note that your access to and use of the Services may be subject to certain third party terms and conditions and privacy policies, including but not limited to application stores, mobile software platforms, online gaming platforms, social networking services and payment providers. You recognize and agree that Pili Pop Labs is not liable for any such third party terms and conditions and their use of your personal data.
Safeguards
Pili Pop Labs follows generally accepted industry standards and maintains reasonable safeguards to attempt to ensure the security, integrity and privacy of the information in Pili Pop Labs’ possession. Only those persons with a need to process your personal data in connection with the fulfillment of their tasks in accordance with the purposes of this Privacy Policy and for the purposes of performing technical maintenance, have access to your personal data in Pili Pop Labs’ possession. Personal data collected by Pili Pop Labs is stored in secure operating environments that are not available to the public. However, no system can be 100% secure and there is the possibility that despite Pili Pop Labs’ reasonable efforts, there could be unauthorized access to your personal data. By using the Services, you assume this risk.
Other
Pili Pop Labs is not responsible for any personal data you choose to make public.
Pili Pop Labs takes children’s privacy seriously, and encourages parents and/or guardians to play an active role in their children’s online experience at all times. Pili Pop Labs may store and/or transfer your personal data to its affiliates and partners in and outside of EU/EEA member states in accordance with mandatory legislation and this Privacy Policy. Pili Pop Labs may disclose your personal data to third parties in connection with a corporate merger, consolidation, restructuring, the sale of substantially all of Pili Pop Labs’ stock and/or assets or other corporate change, including, without limitation, during the course of any due diligence process provided, however, that this Privacy Policy shall continue to govern such personal data.
Links
You may have the opportunity to follow links on the Site to other site that may be of interest to you. Pili Pop Labs endeavors to only link to reputable organizations. Because other site may not be hosted or controlled by Pili Pop Labs, we are not responsible for the privacy practices of those sites or the content provided thereon. Therefore, the privacy policies with respect to other site may differ from those applicable to the Site. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of each other site. This Privacy Policy only applies to information collected and maintained by Pili Pop Labs.
Notice of Privacy Rights of French Residents
In accordance with section 2 in chapter 5 of the new French law dated August 06, 2004, concerning “the protection of individuals with regard to the processing of personal information”, you have a right to access, modify, rectify and delete data concerning you. In order to do so, please contact Pili Pop Labs at support@pilipop.com. Pili Pop Labs will need sufficient information from you to establish your identity and to verify your access request, and also to assist us in handling your request. Requests will be processed as soon as possible. Please note that even if personal data is changed or deleted according to your request, Pili Pop Labs may still retain some of your personal data to resolve disputes, enforce Pili Pop Labs user agreement(s), and comply with technical and legal requirements and constraints related to the security, integrity and operation of Pili Pop Labs Services.
Our privacy policy may change from time to time. If we make any material changes to our policies, we will place a prominent notice on our website or application. If the change materially affects registered users, we will send a notice to you by email, push notification or text.
